Reasoning: The paper discusses a CAD-based human-robot interface for intuitive robot programming, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of sensory feedback to adjust robot paths during operation suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also mentions the minimization of uncertainty, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of CAD packages in manufacturing companies suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for automation and optimization.
